[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to install SecurityManager, but on Java 21, it seems System.setSecurityManager is unsupported. It's terminally deprecated, yet still allowed under certain conditions. From JDK 18 onward, it throws an UnsupportedOperationException unless the system property java.security.manager is set to "allow". I’m curious if I can pass certain JVM arguments for tests under a native image, even though SecurityManager support might be limited there. I should also check if existing tests use a non-null SecurityManager at runtime.
